{"nodes":[{"pos":[32,61],"content":"Request for quotations (RFQs)","needQuote":true,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"Request for quotations (RFQs)","pos":[0,29]}]},{"pos":[75,558],"content":"This article provides an overview of requests for quotation (RFQs), which organizations issue when they must purchase items or services, and want to receive competitive offers from several vendors. In an RFQ, you ask vendors to provide the prices and delivery times for the item quantities that you specify. You can also ask vendors to specify whether there are any incidental charges, such as shipping costs, or any discounts for large orders or early payment of the vendor invoice.","needQuote":true,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"This article provides an overview of requests for quotation (RFQs), which organizations issue when they must purchase items or services, and want to receive competitive offers from several vendors. In an RFQ, you ask vendors to provide the prices and delivery times for the item quantities that you specify. You can also ask vendors to specify whether there are any incidental charges, such as shipping costs, or any discounts for large orders or early payment of the vendor invoice.","pos":[0,483],"nodes":[{"content":"This article provides an overview of requests for quotation (RFQs), which organizations issue when they must purchase items or services, and want to receive competitive offers from several vendors.","pos":[0,197]},{"content":"In an RFQ, you ask vendors to provide the prices and delivery times for the item quantities that you specify.","pos":[198,307]},{"content":"You can also ask vendors to specify whether there are any incidental charges, such as shipping costs, or any discounts for large orders or early payment of the vendor invoice.","pos":[308,483]}]}]},{"pos":[1185,1214],"content":"Request for quotations (RFQs)","linkify":"Request for quotations (RFQs)","nodes":[{"content":"Request for quotations (RFQs)","pos":[0,29]}]},{"content":"This article provides an overview of requests for quotation (RFQs), which organizations issue when they must purchase items or services, and want to receive competitive offers from several vendors.","pos":[1216,1413]},{"content":"In an RFQ, you ask vendors to provide the prices and delivery times for the item quantities that you specify.","pos":[1414,1523]},{"content":"You can also ask vendors to specify whether there are any incidental charges, such as shipping costs, or any discounts for large orders or early payment of the vendor invoice.","pos":[1524,1699]},{"content":"The request for quotation (RFQ) process covers the following tasks:","pos":[1701,1768]},{"content":"Creating and sending an RFQ to one or more vendors","pos":[1774,1824]},{"content":"Receiving and registering RFQ replies (bids)","pos":[1829,1873]},{"content":"Transferring accepted bids to a purchase order, purchase agreement, or purchase requisition","pos":[1878,1969]},{"content":"The following illustration provides an overview of the RFQ process.","pos":[1971,2038]},{"pos":[2042,2135],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ph id=\"ph1\">![</ph>Request for quotation process<ept id=\"p1\">](./media/rfq-process-458x1024.jpg)](./media/rfq-process.jpg)</ept>","source":"[![Request for quotation process](./media/rfq-process-458x1024.jpg)](./media/rfq-process.jpg)"},{"content":"You can create an RFQ from planned orders, from a purchase requisition, or from a manual entry.","pos":[2139,2234]},{"content":"The RFQ that you create is called an RFQ case, and this is the base document that you use to issue an RFQ to each vendor.","pos":[2235,2356]},{"content":"After you prepare the RFQ case and add vendors, click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Send<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> on the RFQ case, and an RFQ journal is generated for each vendor that you sent the RFQ to.","pos":[2357,2510],"source":" After you prepare the RFQ case and add vendors, click **Send** on the RFQ case, and an RFQ journal is generated for each vendor that you sent the RFQ to."},{"content":"You can configure the print management settings for the Send action to either print a report for each vendor to an archive or send a report to each vendor's email address.","pos":[2511,2682]},{"content":"In addition, the RFQ journal for each vendor can be used to generate a report that you can send or resend to a vendor later.","pos":[2683,2807]},{"content":"You can also configure the Send action to generate a reply sheet that the vendor can fill out.","pos":[2808,2902]},{"content":"If you must amend an RFQ after you send it, you can resend the RFQ to vendors when you've finished.","pos":[2906,3005]},{"content":"When you receive bids, you must enter them on the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Request for quotation replies<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page.","pos":[3009,3098],"source":"When you receive bids, you must enter them on the **Request for quotation replies** page."},{"content":"If you select the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Copy data to reply<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> option, data such as the quantity and dates from the RFQ case is copied into the reply.","pos":[3099,3227],"source":" If you select the **Copy data to reply** option, data such as the quantity and dates from the RFQ case is copied into the reply."},{"content":"You can change this data to reflect the vendor's bid.","pos":[3228,3281]},{"content":"If a second iteration of a reply is required for a particular vendor, click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Return<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> on the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Request for quotation reply<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> page.","pos":[3285,3416],"source":"If a second iteration of a reply is required for a particular vendor, click **Return** on the **Request for quotation reply** page."},{"content":"The Return action generates a new journal and a report that will be printed, archived, and sent according to your print management settings.","pos":[3417,3557]},{"content":"If you added scoring criteria to your RFQ case, the RFQ reply will have a scoring panel where you can enter the scores.","pos":[3561,3680]},{"content":"The total scores will appear when you compare the replies on the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Compare replies<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page, where you can also compare other reply data, such as the line price, delivery date, and total price.","pos":[3681,3872],"source":" The total scores will appear when you compare the replies on the **Compare replies** page, where you can also compare other reply data, such as the line price, delivery date, and total price."},{"content":"After you decide on a bid or partial bids, you can accept them and reject the rest.","pos":[3876,3959]},{"content":"Acceptance journals, rejection journals, and corresponding reports are generated.","pos":[3960,4041]},{"content":"These will be printed, archived, and sent according to your print management settings.","pos":[4042,4128]},{"content":"When you accept a bid or specific lines in a bid, either a purchase agreement or purchase order is generated, or a purchase requisition is updated, depending on the RFQ purchase type.","pos":[4129,4312]},{"content":"You can create a trade agreement that you can use later for any of the replies, regardless of whether you accepted or rejected them.","pos":[4313,4445]},{"content":"The status of an RFQ appears in the RFQ header and depends on the status of the RFQ lines.","pos":[4449,4539]},{"content":"The status indicates the extent to which you've processed the RFQ.","pos":[4540,4606]},{"content":"Each RFQ has two values for the status: lowest and highest.","pos":[4607,4666]},{"content":"The lowest status is the least advanced stage of any line in the RFQ, and the highest status is the most advanced stage of any line in the RFQ.","pos":[4667,4810]},{"content":"For example, if the least advanced stage in an RFQ is for a line that has been created, the lowest status for the RFQ is <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Created<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.","pos":[4811,4944],"source":" For example, if the least advanced 